##basic kubectl commands

1. Check cluster info
kubectl cluster-info

2. See all nodes in the cluster
kubectl get nodes

3. See all pods
kubectl get pods

All pods in all namespaces
kubectl get pods -A

4. Describe a pod

(Shows details, logs, events)

kubectl describe pod <pod-name>

5. Check logs of a pod
kubectl logs <pod-name>

6. Apply a YAML file (create/update resources)
kubectl apply -f file.yaml

7. Delete a resource
kubectl delete -f file.yaml

Delete a pod directly
kubectl delete pod <pod-name>

8. Create a deployment
kubectl create deployment myapp --image=nginx

9. Check deployments
kubectl get deployments

10. Expose deployment as a service
kubectl expose deployment myapp --type=NodePort --port=80

11. View all services
kubectl get svc

12. Edit a running resource
kubectl edit deployment myapp

13. Scale deployment
kubectl scale deployment myapp --replicas=3

14. Delete a deployment
kubectl delete deployment myapp
